Why would it be unrealistic / unproductive  to memorize Slick syntax - what
are the skills we were trying to practice?
We are trying to think how a computer thinks. Its like learning a new
language, you dont memorize every single word, you use it in everyday life
and it slowly builds and you are able to adapt it to certain things.

What is an array?
An array is a container that holds a number of values from that type

How do you make an array? Give an example.
int array[] = new int[10];

What is an ArrayList?
arraylist is a group of arrays or objects created that have similar or same
values.

How do you make an arraylist?
public ArrayList<Item> stuff = new ArrayList();

In Netbeans, make an arraylist. Use autocompletion with the created arraylist
(the '.' and pop-up):
What are three useful arraylist methods that you identified?
int,boolean,String

What is the difference between an array and an arraylist?
you cant change the size of an array once set but you can for a arraylist

How could we make a health counter for an avatar?
public static int health = 100000;
